<event name="NEBULA_SALT_QUEST">
	<beaconType id="map_icon_merchantquest_major" global="true">
        <color r="155" g="90" b="205" a="1.0"/>
        <unvisitedTooltip>This is the location of a quest from the Traveling Merchant.</unvisitedTooltip>
        <visitedTooltip>Explored location. Nothing left of interest.</visitedTooltip>
    </beaconType>
	<preventFleet/>
	<quest>
		<nebulaBeacon>true</nebulaBeacon>
		<createNebula>false</createNebula>
		<aggressive>2</aggressive>
	</quest>
	<text>Through a clearing in the nebula you find, of all things, a massive crystallized asteroid, but nothing of the Salt Man you're looking for. Still, this is where Sylvan said he must be...</text>
	<img back="BACK_EVENT_LIGHTNEBULA" planet="NONE"/>
	<status type="loss" target="player" system="sensors" amount="1"/>
	<environment type="asteroid"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>The Salt Man might not be here, but we can take advantage of this asteroid.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You approach the asteroid, marveling at the sheer size of it. It's almost as large as your ship! That's when you come to a realization - it IS a ship! It remains motionless as you approach, and you suspect it might be empty.</text>
			<ship load="SHIP_SALT_ABANDONED" hostile="false"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Test out your theory and send some crew aboard.</text>
				<event>
					<text>It seems much like your previous asteroid theory, the empty ship theory is also untrue. A skeleton crew of various races rises to meet you. "Crap, looks like one of the Guild's bounty hunters found us while the boss is out! Rally up men, we'll put these mercs in their place!" You can probably get out of this without killing them, but you doubt they'll be willing to talk until you rough up their hull a bit.</text>
					<ship hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Not worth the risk, pull out.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Guess he's gone, no reason to stick around.</text>
		<event>
			<text>Not like Sylvan to ever have wrong information, but what do you know. You don't even know where his information comes from anyways.</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Check the storage.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="SALT_QUEST_COORDS">
	<text>"We were running a mission to take out one of the Guild's less... hospitable dissection centers, when the boss ran into some trouble. He got captured and is held there currently, but we escaped. His last orders were for us to stay here in the ship and hide. We're in no condition for a jailbreak, especially not after this little brawl, but you might just be the man for the job. Here's the coords, good luck."</text>
	<quest event="NEBULA_SALT_QUEST_2"/>
</event>

<event name="NEBULA_SALT_QUEST_2">
	<beaconType id="map_icon_merchantquest_major" global="true">
        <color r="155" g="90" b="205" a="1.0"/>
        <unvisitedTooltip>This is the location of a quest from the Traveling Merchant.</unvisitedTooltip>
        <visitedTooltip>Explored location. Nothing left of interest.</visitedTooltip>
    </beaconType>
	<quest>
		<nebulaBeacon>true</nebulaBeacon>
		<createNebula>false</createNebula>
		<aggressive>2</aggressive>
	</quest>
	<preventFleet/>
	<text>You find yourself in yet another clearing, and see a massive bay. It's very pleasant looking and you aren't sure where the Clansmen could possibly be keeping something as sinister as a "dissection center"... until you look towards the sky.</text>
	<img back="BACK_EVENT_CLANJAIL" planet="NONE"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Wow, that's big.</text>
		<event>
			<text>Indeed, the facility is so massive it blocks out nearly all of the perceivable sky, yet the market down below bustles with life as if there wasn't just a massive foreboding facility floating above them.</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Just fly up to the facility, what could go wrong?</text>
				<event>
					<text>Turns out, many things. As soon as you pass by the barrier to the dissection center's hangar, a massive Anti-ship cannon on the interior swivels to face your ship, and several Clansmen start shouting at you. "The hell you doin' you git? You got a licccensssse to be in here?"</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Of course!</text>
						<event>
							<text>The Clansman takes a moment to look you dead in the eye. "Then how goesss the motto of the guild?"</text>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Rule thy mind, rule they honor!</text>
								<event load="SALT_QUEST_2_MOTTO_WRONG"/>
							</choice>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>A valiant death before a cowardly life!</text>
								<event load="SALT_QUEST_2_MOTTO_WRONG"/>
							</choice>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Who is better is greater than the rest!</text>
								<event load="SALT_QUEST_2_MOTTO_WRONG"/>
							</choice>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>I think YOU just forgot, and you're asking me so that you don't look stupid.</text>
								<event>
									<text>"What? The hell are you-" The Clansman is cut off by one of his friends. "He's right Percccy, DO you know the guild motto?" The Clansman stutters. "W-well... I uh- Well I bet you don't know it either!" The other Clansman brings his tentacle up to the back of his head and scratches nervously. "Yeah... I guessss you're right. Does anyone here know?" All of the other Clansmen in the room look at each other and shake their heads.</text>
									<choice hidden="true">
										<text>Continue...</text>
										<event>
											<text>The Clansman apparently known as Percy turns to you again. "Ah, well. I guessss we gotta find a better interview quessstion for the future. You get a passs for now."</text>
											<choice hidden="true">
												<text>Continue...</text>
												<event load="SALT_QUEST_2_SUCCESS"/>
											</choice>
										</event>
									</choice>
								</event>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
					<choice hidden="true" req="mind">
						<text>(Mind Control) Of course!</text>
						<event>
							<text>Somehow, you had the most brilliant idea of mind controlling... telepathic Slugs. The cannon blasts a hole in your ship, and you're forced to land, drawing in an angry team of guards to meet you.</text>
							<damage amount="5" system="random" effect="breach"/>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Continue...</text>
								<event load="SALT_QUEST_2_STUPID"/>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
					<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CREW_CLAN">
						<text>(Clansman Crew) "Of courssse!"</text>
						<event>
							<text>Your Clansman crew flashes a smile and pulls out his membership card. It always pays to have connections in the right places. Or... wrong places.</text>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Continue...</text>
								<event load="SALT_QUEST_2_SUCCESS"/>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
					<choice hidden="true" req="cloaking">
						<text>(Cloaking) Hide!</text>
						<event>
							<text>Somehow, you had the most brilliant idea of cloaking... indoors. Though your ship vanishes from sight, there's literally nowhere for you to go. The cannon blasts a hole in your ship, and you're forced to uncloak and land where an angry team of guards meet you.</text>
							<damage amount="5" system="random" effect="breach"/>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Continue...</text>
								<event load="SALT_QUEST_2_STUPID"/>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Nah.</text>
						<event>
							<text>The Clansman sighs. "Well, atleassst you're honessst." A team of Clansmen guards storm aboard your ship.</text>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Continue...</text>
								<event load="SALT_QUEST_2_STUPID"/>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="SALT_QUEST_2_MOTTO_WRONG">
	<text>"That'ssss pretty good. But it's alssso wrong. You're lying through your teeth, it's clear asss day mate."</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>No, you're lying.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Ugh, I don't have time for thissss." The Clansman motions for a team of guards to board your ship.</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Check the storage.</text>
				<event load="SALT_QUEST_2_STUPID"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="SALT_QUEST_2_STUPID">
	<text>Several Clansmen dig around your ship, looking for anything suspicious. You wait nervously as they do so.</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Wait for them to finish inspection.</text>
		<event>
			<text>Fortunately, the Clansmen take little interest in your military goods, but even having passed the inspection that still doesn't compensate for the fact you don't have a permit inside the facility. The Clansmen cut you a deal, unaware of your malicious intent once inside, and offer a discounted "temporary" membership for 25 scrap.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Buy the membership.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You have a good feeling this isn't even official nor following guild protocol, and that all of the scrap will be going to these Slugs right here. All the same, it allows you hassle free entry from this point forward - or at least until you break out the Salt Man.</text>
					<item_modify>
						<item type="scrap" min="-25" max="-25"/>
					</item_modify>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="SALT_QUEST_2_SUCCESS"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Refuse.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You aren't willing to pay, which means your journey ends here.</text>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="SALT_QUEST_2_SUCCESS">
	<text>You've finally made your way to the prison hold, labeled "Exotic Creature Containment." You shoot a couple guards on the way, picking up a keycard from one of them, which you use to unlock the Salt Man's cell.</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>You open the cell door, where you find a massive gray creature leaning against a wall as if waiting for you. "I'm going to take a shot in the dark and say you aren't with the Guild, considering that green ooze all over your chest seems like it belongs to a Slug." He sticks out his massive hand. "Name's Obyn, though most just call me 'Salt Man'."</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>You'd be right, Sylvan sent us to find you.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"I- did I hear you correctly? Sylvan, as in THE Sylvan? The traveling merchant? That's the one?" The Salt Man seems to have an air of both excitement and reservation.</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Yeah, that one. With the big spooky ship who says stranger a lot.</text>
						<event>
							<text>"My dearest is here? Oh heavens, I am hardly prepared for such a reunion... I- wait, well where is he?"</text>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Oh... well he's not actually here.</text>
								<event>
									<text>"Oh. That seems fitting. Oh, Sylvan... Regardless, I appreciate the effort you have gone through to save me. Is my crew aware that I am alive, or will you have to be my ride out of here?"</text>
									<choice hidden="true">
										<text>We met them on the way, but no idea if they're coming.</text>
										<event>
											<text>"They'd be smart not to, it's unwise to challenge the orders of their captain, though I would be a little disappointed... Now, let's hurry out of here before the Guild sends in some tougher firepower to stop you."</text>
											<choice hidden="true">
												<text>Continue...</text>
												<event>
													<text>Obyn follows you through the corridors of the facility, where you make your way back to the hangar where your ship is held. You hurry inside and take off from the massive facility and make your way back down to the market.</text>
													<crewMember amount="1" class="salt">Obyn</crewMember>
													<choice hidden="true">
														<text>Continue...</text>
														<event>
															<text>You begin to think you might actually make it out of here without a fight, when a Clansman cruiser jumps in out of nowhere! "Ah, there you are you little fecal droppingsss! Ssstealing from the Guild only endssss you up in one ssspot! A shallow grave!"</text>
															<ship load="SHIP_CLAN_CRUISER" hostile="true"/>
															<choice hidden="true">
																<text>Continue...</text>
																<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
															</choice>
														</event>
													</choice>
												</event>
											</choice>
										</event>
									</choice>
								</event>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="SYLVAN_DOES_AN_EX_MACHINA">
	<text>As more ships approach, underneath the shadow of the massive dissection center, it becomes apparent this is the end. "The EHG hasss had enough of you messsing around in our sssector! Ssssurrender the Sssalt Man or be annihilated!"</text>
	<variable name="ach_boss_clancruiser" op="set" val="1"/>
	<choice hidden="true" req="pilot" blue="false" max_group="0">
		<text>No, screw you! You guys can't even keep a consistent accent!</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Oi! Lad, you don't have to be rude! Anywaysss, you've made your choiccce mate. Time to sssuffer the consssequencc-" The Clansman doesn't get a chance to finish his sentence when an 18 burst salvo takes out his shields then engines, causing him to spiral into a nearby ship and crash into the market below in a fiery ball of destruction!</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event>
					<text>From the sky descends Sylvan's ship, followed by the Salt Man's own cruiser, firing away into the fleet. "Crap crap crap it'sssss Ssssylvan! RUN!" The Clansmen scatter. You knew Sylvan had a particularly... well armed ship, but you didn't think he was strong enough to scare away an entire fleet. Evidently, his departure from the Guild left quite the impression.</text>
					<choice hidden="true" req="salt" blue="false" lvl="1">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event>
							<text>You watch as Sylvan and the Salt cruiser land in front of you. "Sssstranger ssstranger, I knew I could count on you!" Sylvan laughs nervously, then faces Obyn, but before he can speak he's cut off. "If you dare address me as 'stranger' I'll crack open your skull." "Heheh, I wouldn't dream of it Obyn. It'ssss been a long time. How'ssss life?"</text>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Continue...</text>
								<event>
									<text>"Oh you know, just wandering this scum infested sector and being held captive in labs where they mutilate people for the fun of it." "Ah, I think they call that taxidermy. I did alwayssss find it dissstasssteful..." Sylvan pauses. "I'm ssssorry Obyn, for leaving. I didn't think I could bear to sssee you again, after ssso much time, but when I heard you might be in trouble, I came. But I... I wassss sstill too much of a coward, ssso I sssent thessse friendssss of mine inssstead."</text>
									<choice hidden="true">
										<text>Keep listening.</text>
										<event>
											<text>Obyn sighs. "You know, I can't blame you. The life of a ruthless killer and the life of a merchant are... well not that different in this climate, but I'm sure there's some differences somewhere. Now, come here." The two lean in for a hug, though Sylvan keeps enough distance away from their bodies to prevent his flesh from being singed from Obyn's salty exterior. This is quite the ironic relationship, you realize.</text>
											<choice hidden="true">
												<text>Continue...</text>
												<event load="SYLVAN_SALT_REWARD"/>
											</choice>
										</event>
									</choice>
									<choice hidden="true">
										<text>Look guys, this is sweet and all, but could you save the personal stuff for later please?</text>
										<event>
											<text>The two glare at you for a moment, but then Sylvan chuckles. "Ah yesss, I got lossst in the moment again. You have my mossst sssincere thanksss ssstranger! What kind of man would I be if I didn't give you a reward for your efforts!</text>
											<choice hidden="true">
												<text>Continue...</text>
												<event load="SYLVAN_SALT_REWARD"/>
											</choice>
										</event>
									</choice>
								</event>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
					<choice hidden="true" req="salt" blue="false" lvl="0" max_lvl="0">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="SYLVAN_SALT_REWARD_NOCREW"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="salt" blue="false" max_group="1">
		<text>Give up the Salt Man.</text>
		<event>
			<text>The Salt Man turns to you in shock, but you have little choice. You can't take on an entire fleet! You push him forward, where a team of Clansmen pick him up. "Wissse choiccce ssson. Looksss like you'll live to sssee tomorrow after all. But do usss a favor, and don't come back."</text>
			<removeCrew class="salt">
				<clone>false</clone>
				<text>You literally got the Salt Man a few minutes ago and you've already given him up. Good going.</text>
			</removeCrew>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="SYLVAN_SALT_REWARD">
	<loadEventList seeded="true" first="true" generate="true">
		<event name="SYLVAN_SALT_REWARD_OBYN" req="salt" lvl="1"/>
		<event name="SYLVAN_SALT_REWARD_NOCREW" req="salt" lvl="0" max_lvl="0"/>
	</loadEventList>
</event>
<event name="SYLVAN_SALT_REWARD_NOCREW">
	<text>You watch as Sylvan and the Salt cruiser land in front of you. Sylvan understandably remains silent at the moment, but with the help of Obyn's former crew, carry over a large crate of scrap. They transfer over some blueprints for Obyn's vessel as well to you, figuring the Federation might have some use for them. You can tell Sylvan is distraught about losing Obyn, but it's too late now. "Sssstranger, I ssstill have an old gun of hisss on hand. I... I don't think I can keep it around any longer. Sssso, perhapsss it isss bessst if you take it. I don't blame you for thisss, but... oh well."</text>
	<unlockCustomShip silent="false">PLAYER_SHIP_SALT</unlockCustomShip>
	<autoReward level="HIGH">scrap_only</autoReward>
	<weapon name="SALT_LAUNCHER"/>
</event>
<event name="SYLVAN_SALT_REWARD_OBYN">
	<text>Sylvan, with the help of Obyn and his crew, carry over a large crate of scrap. Obyn transfers over some blueprints for his vessel as well to you, figuring the Federation might have some use for them. Sylvan heads back to his ship, but Obyn stands between the three ships with a look of indecision on his face.</text>
	<unlockCustomShip silent="false">PLAYER_SHIP_SALT</unlockCustomShip>
	<autoReward level="HIGH">scrap_only</autoReward>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>Sylvan faces Obyn again. "Sssomething wrong Obyn? You look like you've got a Calthorian brain parasssite. Again." Obyn shrugs. "I've got three choices of ships. To be honest... I'm not sure where my journeys should go next."</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Entice him to go with Sylvan and work out whatever weird relationship they have.</text>
				<event>
					<text>Obyn glances at Sylvan. "Well, I'm not one to object, but it'sss your choiccce Obyn." Obyn shrugs. "Sure, why the hell not. I'll see what life is like, wandering the cosmos selling guns to strangers." Obyn turns to his crew, and addresses the same Rockman from earlier that you spoke with. "Garter, I'm trusting you with my ship. Take good care of it. And you, Federation captain. You have my gratitude. And since I know gratitude is all but an accepted currency in these parts, maybe this weapon will satisfy you as well. Till next time." Obyn salutes, then walks off with Sylvan into his ship, then flies away.</text>
					<weapon name="SALT_LAUNCHER"/>
					<removeCrew class="salt">
						<clone>false</clone>
						<text>The Salt Man cannot be cloned as he is no longer part of your crew, nor dead.</text>
					</removeCrew>
					<choice hidden="true">
