<textList name="NEBULA_CLAN_FIGHT">
	<text>The Exotic Hunter's Guild has many scouts patrolling this sector, alongside its usual hunters. When they spot you here, and recognize you as a Federation ship, they quickly arm themselves for battle. Their reasoning? Either they think you're a threat, or they want to make a coat out of your skin. Or both.</text>
	<text>The silence of the nebula around you is starting to get to you. Fortunately, this beacon appears to be empt- oh wait, it appears you're mistaken. Clansmen inbound!</text>
	<text>You catch a nearby Clansman watching you from a distance. "Well I'll be, that'ssss one fine ssset of teeth mate! I'm gonna make a lovely necklaccce out of thossse!"</text>
	<text>"An MV ssship? Didn't you get the memo? Thissss isss Guild territory! We didn't buy thisss land from the Kleptocracccy jussst to have sssome freakin' interdimenssssional assshole pop in and sssteal all of our prey!"</text>
	<text>A nearby Guild ship approaches, its weapons already charging. You have to admire the courage of these Clansmen, even if it usually ends with them dead.</text>
	<text>"Hey, isss that a sssship over there? Oh crap, it issss!" A Clansman scrambles for his rifle then swerves his ship around to fight you!</text>
	<text>The Clansmen are prestigious hunters who aren't known to pass up the chance for a quality hunt. While you might be a military vessel armed for combat, that doesn't seem to deter the nearby vessel.</text>
</textList>

<event name="STORM_ENCOUNTER_CLAN">
	<text load="NEBULA_CLAN_FIGHT"/>
	<ship load="SHIP_CLAN_FIGHT" hostile="true"/>
	<environment type="storm"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="NEBULA_ENCOUNTER_SLUG_CLAN">
	<text load="NEBULA_SLUG_CLAN_FIGHT"/>
	<ship load="SHIP_SLUG_FIGHT" hostile="true"/>
	<environment type="nebula"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
	</choice>
</event>
<textList name="NEBULA_SLUG_CLAN_FIGHT">
	<text>Usually the Slug ships you expect to see here are property of the Guild, but sometimes standard Kleptocracy citizens make their way to this sector for a bit of hunting. And as usual, looks like you're the one being hunted!</text>
	<text>"Federation! Thisss isss Kleptocraccccy ssspacce. Don't think jussst becaussse the Guild letssss in outsssidersss that you'll be welcomed by ussss!"</text>
	<text>A Slug vessel is inbound! They might not be EHG, but they're still a hostile you need to eliminate or run from!</text>
	<text>"You're the lasssst kill I need to passsss my memberssship exam and become a member of the Guild! Now sssstand ssstill, I'm tired of having to put effort into thisss!"</text>
	<text>There's many Slugs in EHG space, but you didn't expect to see a standard Kleptocracy citizen. Not that you're surprised, but you are mildly displeased that they've already turned hostile!</text>
</textList>

<event name="NEBULA_ENCOUNTER_SHELL_CLAN">
	<text load="NEBULA_SHELL_CLAN_FIGHT"/>
	<ship load="SHIP_SHELL_FIGHT" hostile="true"/>
	<environment type="nebula"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
