			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Check the storage.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="NEBULA_KNIGHT_PROTESTERS" unique="true">
	<text>You jump when a disembodied voice suddenly speaks to you. From behind, a Saboteur uncloaks, wearing a pin of the Knight logo. "You're... an outsssider, right? The one Sssslocknog sssent. Normally I'd kill you on the ssspot, but I think we can work together here. There'ssss sssome pesssky reformisssstss nearby who are trying to overhaul our government. We want them dead. Kill them, I pay you. Deal?"</text>
	<environment type="nebula"/>
	<choice hidden="true">	
		<text>Accept.</text>
		<event>
			<text>The Saboteur leads you to a small moon with a Slug colony where several Slugs are protesting, led by a rogue Clairvoyant vessel. Take out their leader, and the rest will likely shut up.</text>
			<ship load="SHIP_CLAIRVOYANT_PROTESTER" hostile="false"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Attack!</text>
				<event>
					<text>You raise the weapons and engage the ship.</text>
					<ship hostile="true"/> 
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" req="SLUG_NARCOTICS">
				<text>(Slug Narcotics) Bribe the Clairvoyant to turn on its own people.</text>
				<event>
					<text>It seems drugs outweigh any moral quandaries in Slug society. The Clairvoyants take hold of the drugs, then turn their weapons upon the colonists, forcing them to surrender. Behind you, the Knight is so humored by your 'creative' problem solving he offers an even larger reward.</text>
					<remove name="SLUG_NARCOTICS"/>
					<autoReward level="HIGH">standard</autoReward>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">	
		<text>Refuse.</text>
		<event>
			<text>The Saboteur frowns and beams away to whatever ship is hiding nearby in the nebula watching you.</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Check the storage.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="KNIGHT_PROTESTERS_WIN" unique="true">
	<text>The rest of the colony is terrified. "Pleasssse, all we want isss peacce! The Kleptocraccccy isss sssso needlesssly cruel, regardlesss of the king! We want to progressss Sslug sssociety into sssomething the ressst of the galaxy can look at with more than dissstasste!"</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Ignore them and force the colony to surrender.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You ignore the colonists, raising your weapons and firing a warning shot. This sends them running for cover, and inevitably surrendering. The Saboteur returns and thanks you for your help, and rewards you as promised.</text>
			<autoReward level="MED">standard</autoReward>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Kill the Saboteur and free the colony.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You draw your blaster, and quickly spin around to blast the Saboteur. They're faster at first, but quickly get lost in the unfamiliar corridors of your ship and are dispatched with relative ease. Though a future Knight vessel will likely return to prey on the colony, they're free for now, and reward you in a somewhat unconventional way.</text>
			<damage amount="-7"/>
			<upgrade amount="1" system="shields"/>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="BLUELIST_FIRE_ALL">
		<text>(Fire Weapon) Make an example, torch the colony.</text>
		<event>
			<text>In a short period of time, the colony is ablaze and about half of its population dead. It's a gruesome display that will undoubtedly be used as propaganda in the future, but it's had quite the impression on the Saboteur. So amazed at your dedication to the task, he even offers to join your crew!</text>
			<crewMember amount="1" class="slug_saboteur"/>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="NEBULA_KNIGHT_SHAKESPEARE" unique="true">
	<text>"Hail th're did Feed'ration. Though mine own w'rds might beest rough, I asketh thee to holdeth with me. I may give you nay harmeth, lest thee stow thine weapons 'r brandish dram m're than the bravado one might beest accustom'd to. Aye? Art these reasonable t'rms 'r might we beest needing a duel?"</text>
	<environment type="nebula"/>
	<ship load="SHIP_KNIGHT" hostile="false"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>The Slug captain looks at you expectantly, though you don't understand a word he said.</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
