<event name="NEBULA_DISTRESS_KNIGHT_TAXES" unique="true">
	<text>The distress beacon here originates from a small Slug colony, who is being oppressed by a Knighted vessel. You catch a small excerpt from their conversation on the radio. "Thisss iss OUTRAGEOUSSSSS. We haven't been paying taxesss for yearsss! No one doesss. They're merely a concccept, not sssomething you enforccce! Don't tell me that coward Nightsss finally got ssso greedy he'sss going to sssteal hissss own cccitizensss' money too?"</text> 
	<environment type="nebula"/>
	<distressBeacon/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Help the colony.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You intend to liberate the Slug colony, and attack the Knighted vessel.</text>
			<ship load="SHIP_KNIGHT_TAXES" hostile="true"/> 
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Help the Knights.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You fire upon the colony, but in response they send a Clairvoyant ship to deal with you!</text>
			<ship load="SHIP_KNIGHT_TAXES_COLONY" hostile="true"/> 
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">	
		<text>Don't get involved.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You have better things to do than help Slugs commit tax evasion.</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Check the storage.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="KNIGHT_TAXES_COLONYHELP">
	<text>The colony is grateful for your help. "Thankssss. Under Sssslocknog, there were no taxesss, we all got along jussst fine and the government got itsss money from extorting other nationsss. Like it sssshould be! Nightsss doesssn't even want the money to run the Kleptocracy, he just wantsss to ssspend it all on liquor and a mate." The colony brings out a weapon they've been keeping for defensive purposes but no longer need thanks to you.</text>
	<autoReward level="HIGH">weapon</autoReward>
</event>
<event name="KNIGHT_TAXES_KNIGHTHELP">
	<text>Without their ship, the colony surrenders to the Knights. After their taxes have been collected and a few fugitives rounded up, the Knights contact you next. "The hell wasss that? You're probably looking for a reward. Uh... here, have one of the criminalssss. We'll just tell Knightsss they died of some obssscure disssseasse that rapidly decaysss the body or sssomething."</text>
	<crewMember amount="1" weapons="1" class="slug"/>
</event>

<event name="NEBULA_DISTRESS_KNIGHT_SHELLSPY" unique="true">
	<text>Surprisingly, it seems a Shell Radiant ship has found their way into the nebula here. They hail you, requesting aid.</text>
	<environment type="nebula"/>
	<distressBeacon/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Receive their request.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Oh good Federation captain, please help! We're here on a mission for thhhhhe Geniocracy to observe the Slug operations, but our commander was taken hostage! Could you track down the shhhip that took thhhhhem and bring thhhem back?"</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Agree.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You plunge further into the nebula until you find the ship they were talking about, but they're already prepared for an attack and lock onto you immediately!</text>
					<ship load="SHIP_KNIGHT_SHELLSPY" hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
					<choice req="SLUG_NARCOTICS" hidden="true">
						<text>Bribe them with the narcotics to let the Shells go.</text>
						<event load="KNIGHT_SHELLSPY_BRIBE"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Decline.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Screw helping people, let's murder!</text>
		<event>
			<text>Once again your sadistic tendencies have taken control, and you've abandoned all decency. But no matter, man the weapons!</text>
			<ship load="SHIP_SHELL_ELITE_GENERIC" hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="MORALITY_UPDATE_SHELL_FIGHT"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Ignore the Shells.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You aren't here to participate in random side quests.</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Check the storage.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
